Friendly Fires is the debut eponymous album by Friendly Fires.
It is to be released on 1 September 2008 in the UK. All tracks
are produced by the band themselves, apart from the opening
track "Jump in the Pool", which was produced by Paul Epworth

Friendly Fires comprises singer Ed MacFarlane, drummer Jack Savidge, and guitarist Edd Gibson.
